Interface PrimitiveCollection<E>

    public interface PrimitiveCollection<E>
extends PrimitiveCollectable<E>, Collection<E>
    Base interface for all primitive collection interfaces.

    This interface extends Collection allowing seamless integration with other APIs. All Collection methods can be used, using the primitive wrapper class. However, it will be much more efficient to use the direct primitive methods in the subinterface.

    Since:
    1.0

      • containsAny

        boolean containsAny(Collection<?> values)
        Checks if this collection contains any of the values in the specified collection. If the specified collection is empty, false is returned.
        Parameters:
        values - the values to search for, null treated as empty collection
        Returns:
        true if at least one of the values is found
